      <p style="font-size:13.5px;color:#6b6b68">CIS Critical Security Controls v8. Published by the Center for Internet Security (CIS) — a nonprofit organization. Released May 2021. 18 Controls and 153 Safeguards. Free and publicly available. Evidence-based: originally developed from real attack data analyzed by US government security agencies. Prioritized: ordered by security impact. Scalable: three Implementation Groups for organizations of all sizes. Maps to: NIST CSF, HIPAA, HITRUST, SOC 2, ISO 27001, PCI-DSS, and more.</p>
